    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-03T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-03T07:00:00-05:00" n="353"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3980: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-03T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 3, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 3—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>449. Foreign Office advised the Embassy this morning that they have not yet
                    received detailed information desired by the Department which it appears is not
                    readily available and must be assembled from more than one source. It was stated
                    informally, however, that a practically complete embargo already exists on the
                    part of the British Government with respect to the licenses issued prior to May
                    9th.</p>
                <pb facs="0350" n="280" xml:id="pg_280"/>
                <p>All replies so far received to inquiries by the League of Nations (see Embassy’s
                    433, July 26, noon, paragraph 4) have been in the affirmative but certain
                    important countries notably Belgium and other nations have not yet replied.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
